crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a comprehensive information stealer. It exhibits a wide range of malicious behaviors including credential theft from browsers (Chrome, Edge, Firefox), cryptocurrency wallets (Exodus, Electrum, Monero), and messaging applications (Discord, Telegram, Skype). It performs process injection by downloading a malicious DLL ('katz_ontop.dll') from a C2 server and loading it into browser processes using `CreateRemoteThread`. The malware conducts extensive system reconnaissance, captures screenshots, steals Wi-Fi passwords via `netsh`, and exfiltrates the stolen data to a C2 server. Finally, it attempts to delete itself to cover its tracks. Key IOCs include the IP `31.177.109.39` and the domain `twist2katz.com`.
